          <text>
                    <body>
                              <pb n="1"/>
                              <p>
                                        <add>Yiddish</add>
                              </p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)"><addressee>Mr Rev I. Leeser Esq</addressee>;</p>
                              <p>
                                        <add>Yiddish</add>
                              </p>
                              <p>
                                        <persName role="author">N. Ottinger</persName>
                              </p>
                              <p>
                                        <placeName>161 Division <sic>stret</sic></placeName>
                              </p>
                              <pb n="2"/>
                              <p>
                                        <add>Yiddish</add>
                              </p>
                              <p rend="align(right)">
                                        <date>Fri<lb/> July 8, 1853</date>
                              </p>
                              <p rend="indent(9)"><placeName>New York</placeName>, <date>Thursday,
                                                  2<hi rend="sup">nd</hi> Day of<lb/> Rosh Hodesh
                                                  Tammuz, 1853</date></p>
                              <p rend="indent(10)">
                                        <addressee>Mr. Rev. I. Leeser Esq.</addressee>
                              </p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">I am very much surprised that I<lb/> have not
                                        heard from you in so long. I hope<lb/> things are right with
                                        you, and that you<lb/> are well. I can say this about myself
                                        and<lb/> my family. Thank God.</p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">Again I want some books, namely</p>
                              <p>6 prayer-books German ritual</p>
                              <p>3     “         “      Sephardic</p>
                              <p>  bound in usual binding</p>
                              <p>3 Pentateuchs of your own in leather<lb/> without gilt</p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">I hope you will send me everything<lb/> at lowest
                                        price. Again I want to be<lb/> advertised in the Occident.
                                        Nothing more</p>
                              <p rend="indent(9)">With best wishes,</p>
                              <p rend="indent(9)">your friend,</p>
                              <p rend="indent(9)">
                                        <persName role="author">N. Ottinger</persName>
                              </p>
                              <p rend="indent(9)">
                                        <placeName>161 Division St.</placeName>
                              </p>
